  /* ============================================================================
     ===== Phase 9.2.2 — Studio Qualification Form Builder (Phase 2 of 7) =======
     ============================================================================
     Three new master tables that power the Qualification Form feature.

     These are STRUCTURED domain tables (plain arrays of records), not the
     flexible-schema {columns, rows} catalogs. The shape is fixed because
     questionnaire templates have meaningful, non-arbitrary fields.

     Tables:
       MasterQuestionnaireTemplates  — 5 templates, one per prospect type
       MasterQuestionnaireQuestions  — 80 questions (15+15+16+17+17), keyed by templateId
       QuestionnaireResponses        — empty, ready for Phase 4 submissions

     Each question has:
       id           — unique numeric ID
       templateId   — FK to MasterQuestionnaireTemplates.id
       order        — 1-based display order within the template
       text         — the question wording (English)
       textHi       — Hindi translation slot (empty for now, Phase 7+)
       type         — single-select | multi-select | short-text | long-text |
                      number | range | yes-no | date | composite | file
       weight       — 0-10 importance for the qualification score
       required     — boolean
       options      — array of choices for select-types; null otherwise
       scoringMap   — object mapping each option value → multiplier 0.0-1.0,
                      used to compute weighted score. For non-select types
                      a function-name reference or null.
       whyItMatters — internal note shown to the studio admin in the editor
       placeholder  — input placeholder text (short-text / long-text / number)

     Each template has:
       id, code, name, propertyCategory, propertyType (array — empty = all types
       within that category), variant ('standard' for Phase 2 seed), isActive,
       introText (the intro screen copy), outroText (the thank-you copy),
       brandAccent (optional override of studio accent for this form's UI),
       estimatedMinutes, createdOn.

     Each response has:
       id, templateId, prospectName, prospectPhone, prospectEmail, prospectCity,
       projectCategory, propertyType, sourceChannel ('whatsapp' | 'email' |
       'instagram' | 'direct'), shareableLinkId (the public URL slug),
       status ('link_sent' | 'link_opened' | 'started' | 'completed' |
       'abandoned' | 'converted' | 'archived'), answers (array of
       {questionId, value, answeredAt}), scoreTotal, scoreMaxPossible,
       scorePct, tier ('hot' | 'warm' | 'cold'), createdOn, lastActivityOn,
       completedOn, convertedToProjectId.
     ============================================================================ */

